      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lowville%2C_New_York"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Black River Canal opened in 1851, followed by railroads in 1867 and 1906, sparking industrial growth that included a world‑leading bowling pin maker.",
